    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I set spellfile like this:\r\n`vim.opt.spellfile=\"~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add\"`\r\nI receive an error:\r\nE484: Can't open file ~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add\r\n\r\nBUT, when I do this vim-way:\r\n`vim.cmd('set spellfile=~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add')`\r\nI receive no error.\r\nDirectory has all needed permissions and file exists.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n`i` woooord\r\n`esc`\r\n:lua vim.opt.spellfile=\"\\~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add\"\r\nzg\r\n-- Receive an error\r\n:set spellfile=~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add\r\nzg\r\n-- Word 'woooord' added to ~/.config/nvim/spell/en.utf-8.add\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBoth solutions should work.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno lua support in Vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 23.05.3759.261abe8a44a7 (Stoat)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nnix package",
